title: New products, markets add value for Texas timber - Texas Farm Bureau
summary: The Texas timber industry is experiencing changes in product demand and market forces. New products like cross-laminated mass timbers and carbon sequestration are enhancing the value of trees. Texas A&M Forest Service is working with landowners to navigate these changes and manage their timber tracts sustainably.

title: The ultimate surf + turf: Innovative commercial baking process-meets-climate smart seaweed gains patent - BakeryAndSnacks.com
summary: Sea & Flour produces patented seaweed-enhanced bread and baked goods that are healthier, more sustainable, and better for the environment than traditional products. The company's novel process for incorporating seaweed into commercial baking has earned it a US patent. Sea & Flour's products are a green innovation because they reduce sodium content, are a rich source of essential vitamins and minerals, and have a carbon-negative footprint.

title: Healy is just one of the newer, weirder multi-level marketing schemes - OnlySky Media
summary: The Healy is a new multi-level marketing product that claims to send vibes of various natures to its wearer. It is promoted as a cure-all for everything from autism to chronic pain to depression to infertility to basic cuts and scrapes. However, the FDA has approved use only as a TENS unit, and there is no scientific evidence to support any of the other claims made about it.

title: Centre releases fact sheet to promote agroforestry - Hindustan Times
summary: The Indian government has published a list of 36 species that can be grown in different agro-climatic zones for agroforestry systems and home gardens. Agroforestry practices include farm profitability, environmental advantages, and increasing the area under green cover, enhancing the carbon sink, and reducing the biotic pressure on forests. While the article provides information on agroforestry practices, it does not describe a specific product or process innovation.
